    "def example_analyze_single_list():\n",
    "    \"\"\"Demonstrate single gene list analysis.\"\"\"\n",
    "    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n",
    "    print(\"Example 4: Analyze Single Gene List\")\n",
    "    print(\"=\"*60)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # T-cell marker genes\n",
    "    t_cell_genes = [\"CD3E\", \"CD3D\", \"CD8A\", \"GZMK\", \"PRF1\", \"IFNG\"]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n--- Analyzing genes: {t_cell_genes} ---\")\n",
    "    df = piaso.tl.analyzeMarkers(t_cell_genes, species=\"Human\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"Found {len(df)} cell type matches\")\n",
    "    if len(df) > 0:\n",
    "        print(\"\\nTop 5 matches:\")\n",
    "        print(df[['cell_type', 'matched_gene_count', 'avg_specificity']].head())"
   ]

    "# results, top_hits = piaso.tl.analyzeMarkers(gene_sets, species=\"Mouse\")\n",
    "results, top_hits = piaso.tl.analyzeMarkers(gene_sets)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nCell Type Predictions:\")\n",
    "for cluster, cell_type in top_hits.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"  {cluster}: {cell_type}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show detailed results\n",
    "print(f\"\\n--- Detailed results for Cluster_0 ---\")\n",
    "if 'Cluster_0' in results and len(results['Cluster_0']) > 0:\n",

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b3b19915-3b82-4276-a67e-a56b8c359f61",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### COSG integration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "53635228-2bb7-455d-8170-9a20330b6b30",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The piaso.tl.analyzeMarkers function will infer the cell types for each cluster or cell group based on the top marker genes identified by the marker gene identification method [COSG](https://github.com/genecell/COSG) and the cell type marker genes collected in [PIASOmarkerDB](https://piaso.org/piasomarkerdb)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "78dce069-857c-4a30-8085-6afaee48f935",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "##### Run COSG"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "3cc02cae-0260-49b1-8241-9024cdd19913",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import cosg"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "144389d4-d3b6-4376-bdcf-afe1c5602a84",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "You could set groupby to `Leiden`, here is using the manually annotated cell type column as a demo:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "id": "de099001-a195-4752-a770-2f24e1f95500",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Finished identifying marker genes by COSG, and the results are in adata.uns['cosg'].\n",
      "CPU times: user 2.54 s, sys: 366 ms, total: 2.9 s\n",
      "Wall time: 2.91 s\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "%%time\n",
    "groupby='CellTypes'\n",
    "cosg.cosg(adata,\n",
    "    key_added='cosg',\n",
    "    use_raw=False, layer='log1p', ## e.g., if you want to use the log1p layer in adata\n",
    "    mu=100,\n",
    "    expressed_pct=0.1,\n",
    "    remove_lowly_expressed=True,\n",
    "    n_genes_user=adata.n_vars, ### Use all the genes, to enable the calculation of transformed COSG scores\n",
    "    # n_genes_user=100,\n",
    "    groupby=groupby,\n",
    "    return_by_group=True,\n",
    "    verbosity=1\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "016e4935-ed13-47c1-832e-0d958c136dd3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
